{
  "video_id": "cDly3bkAAj4",
  "title": "Everything Wrong With Windows 10 | Untangled",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 360.0,
      "end_time": 2980.0,
      "text": "I've been a Windows user since Windows 98,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2980.0,
      "end_time": 5770.0,
      "text": "and even though I work eight hours a day on a Mac,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5770.0,
      "end_time": 8160.0,
      "text": "my favorite OS is still Windows."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8160.0,
      "end_time": 10000.0,
      "text": "It has the broadest app support."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10000.0,
      "end_time": 11930.0,
      "text": "It's the best option for gamers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 11930.0,
      "end_time": 13870.0,
      "text": "and if you wanna build your own computer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 13870.0,
      "end_time": 17000.0,
      "text": "it's basically your only option. Sorry, Linux."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 17000.0,
      "end_time": 20640.0,
      "text": "Windows 10 has improved a lot since its 2015 release,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20640.0,
      "end_time": 22310.0,
      "text": "and in January, it overtook"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 22310.0,
      "end_time": 25419.0,
      "text": "Windows 7 as the most-used desktop operating system"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 25420.0,
      "end_time": 27810.0,
      "text": "in the world. But it isn't perfect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 27810.0,
      "end_time": 30113.0,
      "text": "and Windows 10 still has a long way to go."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 33100.0,
      "end_time": 36320.0,
      "text": "The most obvious issues in Windows 10 are with the design."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36320.0,
      "end_time": 38520.0,
      "text": "Windows 8 was a huge design change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38520.0,
      "end_time": 41400.0,
      "text": "but Microsoft went too far towards touch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 41400.0,
      "end_time": 44100.0,
      "text": "which made traditional desktop work cumbersome."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44100.0,
      "end_time": 46769.0,
      "text": "With Windows 10, Microsoft combined the looks"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46770.0,
      "end_time": 48410.0,
      "text": "of Windows 7 and 8."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 48410.0,
      "end_time": 51129.0,
      "text": "The Start menu and notifications got a refresher,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 51130.0,
      "end_time": 53210.0,
      "text": "we lost the Charms menu from Windows 8,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 53210.0,
      "end_time": 55160.0,
      "text": "and Windows apps stuck around."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 55160.0,
      "end_time": 56610.0,
      "text": "But this combination of styles"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 56610.0,
      "end_time": 58670.0,
      "text": "and functions caused a slew"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 58670.0,
      "end_time": 61680.0,
      "text": "of design inconsistencies across the UI."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 61680.0,
      "end_time": 62750.0,
      "text": "There's a big difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 62750.0,
      "end_time": 64890.0,
      "text": "in appearance between modern Windows apps"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 64890.0,
      "end_time": 66680.0,
      "text": "and classic Windows."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 66680.0,
      "end_time": 69540.0,
      "text": "The new Windows Settings page may be the first thing you see"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 69540.0,
      "end_time": 72190.0,
      "text": "if you want to adjust your display or sound settings."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 72190.0,
      "end_time": 74570.0,
      "text": "But if you want to dig a little deeper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 74570.0,
      "end_time": 76460.0,
      "text": "you're taken to a Control Panel window"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 76460.0,
      "end_time": 79350.0,
      "text": "that has barely changed since the '90s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 79350.0,
      "end_time": 80619.0,
      "text": "and the older design language"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 80620.0,
      "end_time": 83640.0,
      "text": "of Windows often looks better than the new UI."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 83640.0,
      "end_time": 85410.0,
      "text": "With Windows 10, Microsoft"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 85410.0,
      "end_time": 87640.0,
      "text": "is slowly replacing the Metro Design used"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 87640.0,
      "end_time": 91000.0,
      "text": "in Windows 8 with what it calls Fluent Design."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 91000.0,
      "end_time": 92290.0,
      "text": "But a lot of these apps just look"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 92290.0,
      "end_time": 95100.0,
      "text": "like they couldn't decide between touch and mouse input."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 95100.0,
      "end_time": 96920.0,
      "text": "These two designs are way too different to"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 96920.0,
      "end_time": 98370.0,
      "text": "try to combine together."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 98370.0,
      "end_time": 100110.0,
      "text": "There are huge gaps, and"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 100110.0,
      "end_time": 103300.0,
      "text": "buttons often don't do what you expect them to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 103300.0,
      "end_time": 105800.0,
      "text": "The design of Windows apps like Mail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 105800.0,
      "end_time": 107610.0,
      "text": "Calendar, and Photos feels incomplete"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 107610.0,
      "end_time": 109280.0,
      "text": "years after being released."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 109280.0,
      "end_time": 111780.0,
      "text": "This problem also extends to context menus."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 111780.0,
      "end_time": 114820.0,
      "text": "Windows can show you four different context menus."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 114820.0,
      "end_time": 116419.0,
      "text": "These menus are often redundant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 116420.0,
      "end_time": 117870.0,
      "text": "and it can be confusing to figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 117870.0,
      "end_time": 119300.0,
      "text": "where to find each setting."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 119300.0,
      "end_time": 122509.0,
      "text": "Now, to be fair, these are all surface-level issues."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 122510.0,
      "end_time": 123980.0,
      "text": "Besides a little confusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 123980.0,
      "end_time": 126160.0,
      "text": "the design inconsistencies do not prevent you"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 126160.0,
      "end_time": 127509.0,
      "text": "from getting work done,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 127510.0,
      "end_time": 128800.0,
      "text": "but because of these issues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 128800.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131950.0,
      "text": "Windows doesn't feel like a cohesive operating system."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 131950.0,
      "end_time": 134560.0,
      "text": "Apple's OS X hasn't had a major redesign"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 134560.0,
      "end_time": 137100.0,
      "text": "in almost two decades, but everything feels"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 137100.0,
      "end_time": 139799.0,
      "text": "like one complete operating system."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 139800.0,
      "end_time": 142400.0,
      "text": "Besides design, everyone's favorite gripe"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 142400.0,
      "end_time": 144230.0,
      "text": "about Windows 10 is the updates."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 144230.0,
      "end_time": 146760.0,
      "text": "Windows updates are notoriously aggressive."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 146760.0,
      "end_time": 148310.0,
      "text": "They can even reboot a PC"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 148310.0,
      "end_time": 151680.0,
      "text": "without the user ever acknowledging or accepting the update,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 151680.0,
      "end_time": 153260.0,
      "text": "and unless you want to pay 100 bucks"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 153260.0,
      "end_time": 154870.0,
      "text": "to upgrade to the Pro version,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 154870.0,
      "end_time": 156450.0,
      "text": "there is no easy way to turn off"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 156450.0,
      "end_time": 158280.0,
      "text": "or avoid updates completely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 158280.0,
      "end_time": 160740.0,
      "text": "and, yes, updates are important for security"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 160740.0,
      "end_time": 162840.0,
      "text": "and can often bring cool new features,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 162840.0,
      "end_time": 164610.0,
      "text": "but in recent years, the quality control"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 164610.0,
      "end_time": 166850.0,
      "text": "of Windows updates seems to be declining."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 166850.0,
      "end_time": 168350.0,
      "text": "There were multiple reports"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 168350.0,
      "end_time": 171100.0,
      "text": "of the October update deleting user files,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 171100.0,
      "end_time": 174239.0,
      "text": "and after being pulled, it's now several months late."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 174240.0,
      "end_time": 177780.0,
      "text": "Windows 10 normally has big updates in October and April,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 177780.0,
      "end_time": 179870.0,
      "text": "and with each update, Microsoft puts a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 179870.0,
      "end_time": 181500.0,
      "text": "of focus on new features,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 181500.0,
      "end_time": 183490.0,
      "text": "but it feels like Microsoft keeps moving"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 183490.0,
      "end_time": 184850.0,
      "text": "in the wrong direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 184850.0,
      "end_time": 188359.0,
      "text": "Cortana, Windows 10 S, and Edge all failed"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 188360.0,
      "end_time": 191830.0,
      "text": "at their intended uses and are being reimagined and remade."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 191830.0,
      "end_time": 194730.0,
      "text": "They have also put a lot of focus on the Microsoft Store,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 194730.0,
      "end_time": 196299.0,
      "text": "but most of the apps found there"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 196300.0,
      "end_time": 197790.0,
      "text": "are just slimmed-down versions"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 197790.0,
      "end_time": 200579.0,
      "text": "of programs you can already run on Windows."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 200580.0,
      "end_time": 202690.0,
      "text": "In the three years I've been using Windows 10,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 202690.0,
      "end_time": 203870.0,
      "text": "I have never once needed"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 203870.0,
      "end_time": 206440.0,
      "text": "to download an app from the Windows Store."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 206440.0,
      "end_time": 209760.0,
      "text": "Another big concern people have with Windows 10 is privacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 209760.0,
      "end_time": 211940.0,
      "text": "Since its release, Windows 10 has gotten a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 211940.0,
      "end_time": 215340.0,
      "text": "of criticism for aggressive data collection and telemetry."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 215340.0,
      "end_time": 216850.0,
      "text": "Although Microsoft has become"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 216850.0,
      "end_time": 219190.0,
      "text": "a lot more transparent over the last few years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 219190.0,
      "end_time": 221100.0,
      "text": "there are still a lot of tracking settings"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 221100.0,
      "end_time": 222530.0,
      "text": "turned on by default."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 222530.0,
      "end_time": 224600.0,
      "text": "Even with all these issues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 224600.0,
      "end_time": 227140.0,
      "text": "Windows 10 is still an amazing operating system."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 227140.0,
      "end_time": 229209.0,
      "text": "Microsoft introduced great new features"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 229210.0,
      "end_time": 230730.0,
      "text": "like improved app snapping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 230730.0,
      "end_time": 233109.0,
      "text": "virtual desktops, and improved touch support,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 233110.0,
      "end_time": 235840.0,
      "text": "and the company's plan for Windows 10 as a service"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 235840.0,
      "end_time": 237410.0,
      "text": "where users receive free"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 237410.0,
      "end_time": 240530.0,
      "text": "regular updates, like Mac OS, gives it the potential"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 240530.0,
      "end_time": 242790.0,
      "text": "to be the best version of Windows yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 242790.0,
      "end_time": 244410.0,
      "text": "But Microsoft needs to focus"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 244410.0,
      "end_time": 246590.0,
      "text": "on fixing the features they currently have"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 246590.0,
      "end_time": 248950.0,
      "text": "instead of adding dozens of new ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 248950.0,
      "end_time": 250959.0,
      "text": "Oh, and hurry up with the October update"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 250960.0,
      "end_time": 252910.0,
      "text": "so we can get a better screenshot tool."
    }
  ]
}